name: Belly Shiok

reviews.text:
Tried both the peanut porridge and century egg porridge. Peanut porridge is served in a smaller bowl and century egg porridge comes in a bigger bowl. Both comes with a few small peanuts, bits of fishcake and garnishing. Simple affordable and filling meal.
The stall also has long queue that moved quite quickly. Many people ordered the Chee Cheong fun. Will try other items next time.
At 10.30am on weekday, the yam was sold out. Tried the Chee Cheong Fun (minimum 2 pcs) $2. It‚Äôs soft & smooth, and with the sweet sauce, it‚Äôs yummy üòã. Very old school type.
